sportal.com/social/googleplus.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/email/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F18%2Fmanchester-united-ferguson-west-ahm-allardyce&t=Manchester+United+bemoan+lack+of+red+card+for+Andy+Carroll+of+West+Ham\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/email.png\" border=\"0\" /></a></td></tr></table></div><br/><br/><a href=\"http://da.feedsportal.com/r/163644699079/u/49/f/639039/c/34708/s/2ad807e7/a2.htm\"><img src=\"http://da.feedsportal.com/r/163644699079/u/49/f/639039/c/34708/s/2ad807e7/a2.img\" border=\"0\"/></a><img width=\"1\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://pi.feedsportal.com/r/163644699079/u/49/f/639039/c/34708/s/2ad807e7/a2t.img\" border=\"0\"/><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/theguardian/football/rss/~4/D2JRD9CFoBw\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/publication")) "The Guardian") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football")) "Manchester United") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football")) "Football") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/tone")) "News") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football")) "West Ham United") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football")) "Sir Alex Ferguson") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football")) "Premier League") (pubDate nil "Wed, 17 Apr 2013 23:19:53 GMT") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/2013/apr/18/manchester-united-ferguson-west-ahm-allardyce") (dc:creator nil "David Hytner") (dc:subject nil "Football") (dc:date nil "2013-04-17T23:22:11Z") (dc:type nil "Article") (dc:identifier nil "407412022") (media:keywords nil "Premier League, Manchester United, West Ham United, Football, Sir Alex Ferguson") (media:content ((height . "84") (lang . " ") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "140") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Football/Pix/pictures/2013/4/18/1366240643554/eddie-keogh-003.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Eddie Keogh/Reuters") (media:description nil "Manchester United's goalkeeper David de Gea is challenged by West Ham United's Andy Carroll. Photograph: Eddie Keogh/Reuters")) (media:content ((height . "276") (lang . " ") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "460") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Football/Pix/pictures/2013/4/18/1366240650214/eddie-keogh-008.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Eddie Keogh/Reuters") (media:description nil "Manchester United's goalkeeper David de Gea is challenged by West Ham United's Andy Carroll. Photograph: Eddie Keogh/Reuters")) (feedburner:origLink nil "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/2013/apr/18/manchester-united-ferguson-west-ahm-allardyce")) (item nil (title nil "Chelsea sound out Málaga's Manuel Pellegrini about succeeding Benítez") (link nil "http://feeds.guardian.co.uk/~r/theguardian/football/rss/~3/lIvFShyHiCo/chelsea-malaga-manuel-pellegrini-benitez") (description nil "<div class=\"track\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hits.guardian.co.uk/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.4/46358?ns=guardian&pageName=Article%3Achelsea-malaga-manuel-pellegrini-benitez%3A1895614&ch=Football&c3=Guardian&c4=Chelsea+%28Football%29%2CMalaga+%28Football+club%29%2CLa+Liga+%28Football%29%2CFootball%2CSport&c5=Not+commercially+useful%2CPremier+League&c6=Dominic+Fifield&c7=2013%2F04%2F18+12%3A11&c8=1895614&c9=Article&c10=News&c13=&c19=GUK&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=Chelsea+sound+out+M%C3%A1laga%27s+Manuel+Pellegrini+about+succeeding+Ben%C3%ADtez&c66=Sport&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FSport%2FFootball%2FChelsea\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /></div><p class=\"standfirst\">• Chilean coach led Málaga to Champions League last eight<br />• Chelsea will wait to appoint till top-four place decided</p><p>Chelsea returned to the Premier League's top three on Wednesday night <a href=\"\" title=\"\">with a resounding 3-0 victory at Fulham</a>, strengthening their grip on a Champions League qualification place, while reports in Spain suggested the club are making tentative progress in their pursuit of a permanent manager.</p><p>An adviser for the Málaga coach, Manuel Pellegrini, is understood to have met Chelsea officials this week to discuss the possibility of taking up the reins at Stamford Bridge in the summer once Rafael Benítez's interim stewardship has run its course. The Chilean, who has coached at Real Madrid and enjoyed a successful spell with Villarreal, took Málaga to the quarter-finals of the Champions League this term despite continuing financial problems at the Spanish club, before <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/2013/apr/09/borussia-dortmund-malaga-champions-league\" title=\"\">they lost to Borussia Dortmund</a>.</p><p>The 59-year-old speaks good English and is renowned as a disciplinarian who has implemented a brand of attractive, attacking football. His contract with Málaga expires at the end of next season but includes a buy-out clause believed to be set at around £3.4m, though it remains to be seen whether he can be persuaded to swap Spain for Stamford Bridge.</p><p>Chelsea, who appointed Benítez on a seven-month contract to succeed Roberto Di Matteo, intend to make a formal offer to their preferred candidate only once it is clear whether they have qualified for the Champions League. They are sounding out potential managers, with Pellegrini high on their shortlist.</p><p>José Mourinho is another possibility and has made clear his desire to return to London if, as expected, he leaves Real Madrid in the summer. David Moyes, whose contract at Everton expires in June, and the Atlético Madrid coach, Diego Simeone, have also made an impression, while Gianfranco Zola's progress at Watford has been noted even if these remain early&nbsp;days in the Italian's managerial career.</p><p>Benítez's hopes of leaving Chelsea with Champions League football were boosted by a first away success in the league since mid-January, the recalled John Terry scoring twice to defeat Fulham and remind the interim manager of his qualities. Regardless, the former England captain is likely to return to the bench for Sunday's trip to Liverpool. \"The important thing is always the team,\" said Benítez. \"Every player wants to play every game, but they have to realise they can't do that and be 100% in each game.</p><p>\"As for the Champions League, I said a long time ago that the race for the top four would go until the end for the season. It'll be like this and I don't think any of the clubs up there, including Everton, is out of it. Things can change with every game. We have to keep winning our games and keep going.\"</p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/chelsea\">Chelsea</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/malaga\">Málaga</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/laligafootball\">La Liga</a></li></ul></div><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/dominicfifield\">Dominic Fifield</a></div><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/terms-of-service\">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/feeds\">More Feeds</a></div><p style=\"clear:both\" /><img width='1' height='1' src='http://guardian.co.uk.feedsportal.com/c/34708/f/639039/s/2ad86e30/mf.gif' border='0'/><div class='mf-viral'><table border='0'><tr><td valign='middle'><a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/twitter/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F18%2Fchelsea-malaga-manuel-pellegrini-benitez&t=Chelsea+sound+out+M%C3%A1laga%27s+Manuel+Pellegrini+about+succeeding+Ben%C3%ADtez\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/twitter.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/facebook/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F18%2Fchelsea-malaga-manuel-pellegrini-benitez&t=Chelsea+sound+out+M%C3%A1laga%27s+Manuel+Pellegrini+about+succeeding+Ben%C3%ADtez\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/facebook.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/linkedin/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F18%2Fchelsea-malaga-manuel-pellegrini-benitez&t=Chelsea+sound+out+M%C3%A1laga%27s+Manuel+Pellegrini+about+succeeding+Ben%C3%ADtez\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/linkedin.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/gplus/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F18%2Fchelsea-malaga-manuel-pellegrini-benitez&t=Chelsea+sound+out+M%C3%A1laga%27s+Manuel+Pellegrini+about+succeeding+Ben%C3%ADtez\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/googleplus.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/email/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F18%2Fchelsea-malaga-manuel-pellegrini-benitez&t=Chelsea+sound+out+M%C3%A1laga%27s+Manuel+Pellegrini+about+succeeding+Ben%C3%ADtez\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/email.png\" border=\"0\" /></a></td></tr></table></div><br/><br/><a href=\"http://da.feedsportal.com/r/163067849519/u/49/f/639039/c/34708/s/2ad86e30/a2.htm\"><img src=\"http://da.feedsportal.com/r/163067849519/u/49/f/639039/c/34708/s/2ad86e30/a2.img\" border=\"0\"/></a><img width=\"1\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://pi.feedsportal.com/r/163067849519/u/49/f/639039/c/34708/s/2ad86e30/a2t.img\" border=\"0\"/><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/theguardian/football/rss/~4/lIvFShyHiCo\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/publication")) "The Guardian") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football")) "La Liga") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football")) "Football") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport")) "Sport") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/tone")) "News") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football")) "Chelsea") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football")) "Málaga") (pubDate nil "Wed, 17 Apr 2013 23:11:25 GMT") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/2013/apr/18/chelsea-malaga-manuel-pellegrini-benitez") (dc:creator nil "Dominic Fifield") (dc:subject nil "Football") (dc:date nil "2013-04-17T23:14:57Z") (dc:type nil "Article") (dc:identifier nil "407411470") (media:keywords nil "Chelsea, Málaga, La Liga, Football, Sport") (media:content ((height . "84") (lang . " ") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "140") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Football/Pix/pictures/2013/4/18/1366239980995/M-lagas-head-coach-Manuel-003.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Dennis Grombkowski/Bongarts/Getty Images") (media:description nil "Málaga's head coach Manuel Pellegrini at Borussia Dortmund. One of his advisers has met Chelsea. Photograph: Dennis Grombkowski/Bongarts/Getty Images")) (media:content ((height . "276") (lang . " ") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "460") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Football/Pix/pictures/2013/4/18/1366239989485/M-lagas-head-coach-Manuel-008.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Dennis Grombkowski/Bongarts/Getty Images") (media:description nil "Málaga's head coach Manuel Pellegrini at Borussia Dortmund. One of his advisers has met Chelsea. Photograph: Dennis Grombkowski/Bongarts/Getty Images")) (feedburner:origLink nil "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/2013/apr/18/chelsea-malaga-manuel-pellegrini-benitez")) (item nil (title nil "West Ham find their finesse but Manchester United banish demons | David Hytner") (link nil "http://feeds.guardian.co.uk/~r/theguardian/football/rss/~3/Kg58w1M5LXc/west-ham-manchester-united-finesse") (description nil "<div class=\"track\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hits.guardian.co.uk/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.4/11522?ns=guardian&pageName=Article%3Awest-ham-manchester-united-finesse%3A1895511&ch=Football&c3=GU.co.uk&c4=Premier+League+%28Football%29%2CWest+Ham+United+%28Football%29%2CManchester+United+%28Football%29%2CFootball%2CSport&c5=Premier+League&c6=David+Hytner&c7=2013%2F04%2F17+11%3A16&c8=1895511&c9=Blog&c10=Comment&c13=&c19=GUK&c25=Sport+blog&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=West+Ham+find+their+finesse+but+Manchester+United+banish+demons&c66=Sport&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FSport%2FFootball%2FPremier+League\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /></div><p class=\"standfirst\">The Hammers' tactics gave the league leaders a scare but their focus was formidable and this was no replay of 1995</p><p>Every Manchester United fan aged roughly 25 or over remembers precisely where he or she was. They also remember precisely what they said. On 14 May 1995, a spring's afternoon at Upton Park and Andy Cole, confronted by Ludek Miklosko, has the last-gasp chance to win the Premier League title for United. \"Just lift it, Andy,\" they shouted. Or words to that effect. But Cole hits it low at Miklosko, who saves. United draw and Blackburn Rovers are the champions.</p><p>That was when title races were title races, when they went to the wire or, at the very least, made it into May. United's canter to their 20th championship has been a very different story, one that has been marked by a remarkable absence of stress. The demons of Upton Park will always gnaw away at Sir Alex Ferguson but when they threatened to reappear here, after West Ham United scored wonderful goals, United swatted them away. The truth was that even a defeat would hardly have mattered.</p><p>United have come to trade in extreme end-of-season luxuries. Their target now is not only to win but to do so in historic style and despite these dropped points, they could still better Chelsea's record 95 points from 2004-05. When they stand to be crowned is also on the agenda. It could be on Sunday week at Arsenal, which would be particularly sweet for Robin van Persie. United roll on, remorselessly.</p><p>West Ham have enjoyed their own sort of comfort this season. The script for newly promoted teams, particularly those that wriggle up via the play-offs, calls for frayed nerves and regular dips in and out of the relegation plunge pool. But West Ham, perhaps surprisingly for a club with a recent addiction to chaos, have remained above the relegation battle, barely once being mentioned as candidates to slip down.</p><p>Allardyce merits credit for overseeing the steadiness. Before the play-off final against Blackpool at the end of his first season in charge, there had been the genuine feeling among the West Ham support that he should be sacked if the team lost. But he got the job done and these days he has the fans' acceptance, at the very least, if not their outright love for his style.</p><p>If many of his players fit a particular profile, they are certainly united behind him. They talk glowingly of his attention to detail and it was evident in his set-up here, in a tactical duel that he would have relished against his hero Ferguson. He pushed Mohamed Diamé and Kevin Nolan high on to United's defensive midfielders, Phil Jones and Michael Carrick, and his team carried the fight. Allardyce has made West Ham competitive.</p><p>United expected an aerial bombardment and balls up to Andy Carroll were a feature of the West Ham strategy. The tall striker put it about with Nemanja Vidic, Rio Ferdinand and, shudderingly so, David De Gea.</p><p>Ferguson jabbed his finger as he advanced his protest to the fourth official, Andre Marriner, after De Gea had been cleaned out by Carroll following a 45th-minute corner.</p><p>The home team's finesse, though, was apparent, whether in Carroll's early threaded shot that kissed the outside of the far post or the sight of Ricardo Vaz Te tricking outrageously out of a tight spot inside his own area. Their opening goal was not bad, when they broke from the edge of their box. There was the drive of Diamé; a stop-start move from Matt Jarvis to flummox Ferdinand; Carroll's aerial power and Vaz Te's anticipation. And the second, from Diamé's left-footed curler, was a peach.</p><p>Carroll's future is a pressing issue for West Ham and his all-action display provided further evidence as to why. His willingness to battle against the hardest centre-halfs not only endears him to supporters. His team-mates relish the out-ball to him and his hold-up work allows them to squeeze up the pitch. His loan from Liverpool expires at the end of the season and Allardyce has suggested that his wage demands, allied to financial fair play, could make it impossible to make the move permanent.</p><p>And what of Allardyce, who has still to sign his contract extension? The club maintain that there will be no problems, that it is merely a matter of time and yet it has dragged and Allardyce says that he has to be sure of his ability to compete in the summer transfer market before he commits. There has also been the notion that he has wanted to wait until West Ham have 40 points. That could happen here on Saturday against Wigan.</p><p>United's focus was formidable. It has sustained them this season and on each occasion that they fell behind their response bristled with conviction. Shinji Kagawa's balance to tee up Antonio Valencia's goal was beautiful and the second equaliser had been extensively trailed, even if Van Persie might have been marginally offside before he struck his 25th of the season. There was no dramatic finale for United. The job had been done.</p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/premierleague\">Premier League</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/westhamunited\">West Ham United</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/manchester-united\">Manchester United</a></li></ul></div><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/davidhytner\">David Hytner</a></div><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/terms-of-service\">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/feeds\">More Feeds</a></div><p style=\"clear:both\" /><img width='1' height='1' src='http://guardian.co.uk.feedsportal.com/c/34708/f/639039/s/2ad7f141/mf.gif' border='0'/><div class='mf-viral'><table border='0'><tr><td valign='middle'><a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/twitter/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2Fblog%2F2013%2Fapr%2F17%2Fwest-ham-manchester-united-finesse&t=West+Ham+find+their+finesse+but+Manchester+United+banish+demons+%7C+David+Hytner\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/twitter.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/facebook/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2Fblog%2F2013%2Fapr%2F17%2Fwest-ham-manchester-united-finesse&t=West+Ham+find+their+finesse+but+Manchester+United+banish+demons+%7C+David+Hytner\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/facebook.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/linkedin/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2Fblog%2F2013%2Fapr%2F17%2Fwest-ham-manchester-united-finesse&t=West+Ham+find+their+finesse+but+Manchester+United+banish+demons+%7C+David+Hytner\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/linkedin.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/gplus/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2Fblog%2F2013%2Fap