tball, Sport") (media:content ((height . "84") (lang . " ") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "140") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Sport/Pix/pictures/2013/4/17/1366236853584/Soccer---Barclays-Premier-003.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Nick Potts/PA") (media:description nil "The West Ham United manager, Sam Allardyce, loses his temper during his side's draw with Manchester United but got his tactics spot-on to stifle the league leaders. Photograph: Nick Potts/PA")) (media:content ((height . "276") (lang . " ") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "460") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Sport/Pix/pictures/2013/4/17/1366236860087/Soccer---Barclays-Premier-008.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Nick Potts/PA") (media:description nil "The West Ham United manager, Sam Allardyce, loses his temper during his side's draw with Manchester United but got his tactics spot-on to stifle the league leaders. Photograph: Nick Potts/PA")) (feedburner:origLink nil "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/blog/2013/apr/17/west-ham-manchester-united-finesse")) (item nil (title nil "Champions League still within our grasp, says Ramsey") (link nil "http://feeds.guardian.co.uk/~r/theguardian/football/rss/~3/FSJ1tVY_x_U/arsenal-champions-league-aaron-ramsey") (description nil "<div class=\"track\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hits.guardian.co.uk/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.4/48065?ns=guardian&pageName=Article%3Aarsenal-champions-league-aaron-ramsey%3A1895414&ch=Football&c3=Guardian&c4=Arsenal+FC+%28Football%29%2CFootball%2CSport&c5=Premier+League&c6=David+Hytner&c7=2013%2F04%2F17+11%3A00&c8=1895414&c9=Article&c10=News&c13=&c19=GUK&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=Champions+League+still+within+Arsenal%27s+grasp%2C+says+Aaron+Ramsey&c66=Sport&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FSport%2FFootball%2FArsenal\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /></div><p class=\"standfirst\">• 'It was important for us not to lose against Everton'<br />• Win at Fulham would put Arsenal in commanding position</p><p>Aaron Ramsey insists Arsenal's confidence has not been dented by their edgy <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/2013/apr/16/arsenal-everton-premier-league-match-report\" title=\"\">0-0 home draw with Everton on Tuesday night</a> and he believes that a Champions League finish remains within their grasp.</p><p>It is the time of year when supporters scrutinise the permutations of the run-in and players are no different, with Ramsey noting the toughness of the upcoming fixtures for both Chelsea and Tottenham Hotspur, not least the meeting between the rivals at Stamford Bridge on 8 May. It goes without saying that one club will drop points.</p><p>Ramsey, though, is focused on what Arsenal have to do and he says that if they can win at Fulham on Saturday, to end a key week with seven points from an available nine, they would be in a commanding position. <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/2013/apr/13/arsenal-norwich-city-premier-league\" title=\"\">Arsenal beat Norwich City at home last Saturday</a> and the draw against Everton extended their unbeaten run in the Premier League to five matches.</p><p>\"It was important for us not to lose against Everton and we still have a lot of confidence,\" Ramsey said. \"We were quite nervous in the first half and our final ball let us down but, overall, we were quite solid. We're looking forward to the weekend. Tottenham and Chelsea still have to play each other. They still have tough games. The teams are still going to drop points so we're positive and confident that we can finish in the top four.</p><p>\"We always knew that this week was going to be a big week for us and hopefully now we can finish it off strongly and get a win at Fulham. That would put us in a really strong position.\"</p><p>Ramsey has rediscovered his best form in recent weeks and it is no coincidence that he is back to playing in central midfield. \"I'm delighted with the way I'm playing and how the team is playing,\" he said. \"It makes a big difference [being in central midfield]. That's my position and that's where I want to play.</p><p>\"At the beginning of the season, I was moving all over the pitch, playing left-wing, right-wing, right-back. I was asked to do a job in many positions, which I'm happy to do for the team. If the manager wants me to play there, I'm not going to say no to that. But I've got my place back in the middle and my performances have been showing what I'm capable of doing there.\"</p><p>The Football Association will take no action following the fracas between Arsenal's Jack Wilshere and Everton's Kevin Mirallas on Tuesday. The pair clashed in the tunnel at half-time but the governing body is satisfied that it was nothing serious.</p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/arsenal\">Arsenal</a></li></ul></div><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/davidhytner\">David Hytner</a></div><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/terms-of-service\">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/feeds\">More Feeds</a></div><p style=\"clear:both\" /><img width='1' height='1' src='http://guardian.co.uk.feedsportal.com/c/34708/f/639039/s/2ad78d93/mf.gif' border='0'/><div class='mf-viral'><table border='0'><tr><td valign='middle'><a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/twitter/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F17%2Farsenal-champions-league-aaron-ramsey&t=Champions+League+still+within+our+grasp%2C+says+Ramsey\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/twitter.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/facebook/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F17%2Farsenal-champions-league-aaron-ramsey&t=Champions+League+still+within+our+grasp%2C+says+Ramsey\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/facebook.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/linkedin/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F17%2Farsenal-champions-league-aaron-ramsey&t=Champions+League+still+within+our+grasp%2C+says+Ramsey\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/linkedin.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/gplus/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F17%2Farsenal-champions-league-aaron-ramsey&t=Champions+League+still+within+our+grasp%2C+says+Ramsey\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/googleplus.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/email/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F17%2Farsenal-champions-league-aaron-ramsey&t=Champions+League+still+within+our+grasp%2C+says+Ramsey\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/email.png\" border=\"0\" /></a></td></tr></table></div><br/><br/><a href=\"http://da.feedsportal.com/r/163644692613/u/49/f/639039/c/34708/s/2ad78d93/a2.htm\"><img src=\"http://da.feedsportal.com/r/163644692613/u/49/f/639039/c/34708/s/2ad78d93/a2.img\" border=\"0\"/></a><img width=\"1\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://pi.feedsportal.com/r/163644692613/u/49/f/639039/c/34708/s/2ad78d93/a2t.img\" border=\"0\"/><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/theguardian/football/rss/~4/FSJ1tVY_x_U\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/publication")) "The Guardian") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football")) "Arsenal") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football")) "Football") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport")) "Sport") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/tone")) "News") (pubDate nil "Wed, 17 Apr 2013 22:00:01 GMT") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/2013/apr/17/arsenal-champions-league-aaron-ramsey") (dc:creator nil "David Hytner") (dc:subject nil "Football") (dc:date nil "2013-04-17T23:06:43Z") (dc:type nil "Article") (dc:identifier nil "407384280") (media:keywords nil "Arsenal, Football, Sport") (media:content ((height . "84") (lang . " ") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "140") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Football/Pix/pictures/2013/4/17/1366213092421/Arsenals-Aaron-Ramsey-lef-003.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "David Price/Arsenal FC via Getty Images") (media:description nil "Arsenal's Aaron Ramsey, left, is challenged by Marouane Fellaini of Everton during the 0-0 draw at the Emirates. Photograph: David Price/Arsenal FC via Getty Images")) (media:content ((height . "276") (lang . " ") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "460") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Football/Pix/pictures/2013/4/17/1366213099589/Arsenals-Aaron-Ramsey-lef-008.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "David Price/Arsenal FC via Getty Images") (media:description nil "Arsenal's Aaron Ramsey, left, is challenged by Marouane Fellaini of Everton during the 0-0 draw at the Emirates. Photograph: David Price/Arsenal FC via Getty Images")) (feedburner:origLink nil "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/2013/apr/17/arsenal-champions-league-aaron-ramsey")) (item nil (title nil "Arsenal's Jack Wilshere and Everton's Kevin Mirallas avoid FA action") (link nil "http://feeds.guardian.co.uk/~r/theguardian/football/rss/~3/TExmzVkUINY/jack-wilshere-kevin-mirallas-avoid-fa-action") (description nil "<div class=\"track\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hits.guardian.co.uk/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.4/74519?ns=guardian&pageName=Article%3Ajack-wilshere-kevin-mirallas-avoid-fa-action%3A1895609&ch=Football&c3=GU.co.uk&c4=Arsenal+FC+%28Football%29%2CEverton+%28Football%29%2CJack+Wilshere+%28football%29%2CFootball%2CSport&c5=Europa+League%2CPremier+League&c6=Dan+Matthews&c7=2013%2F04%2F17+10%3A59&c8=1895609&c9=Article&c10=News&c13=&c19=GUK&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=Arsenal%27s+Jack+Wilshere+and+Everton%27s+Kevin+Mirallas+avoid+FA+action&c66=Sport&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FSport%2FFootball%2FArsenal\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /></div><p class=\"standfirst\">• Pair clashed at half-time in tunnel at Emirates<br />• Per Mertesacker says fight for fourth place continues</p><p>The Football Association has announced that no action will be taken against Kevin Mirallas or Jack Wilshere after the pair clashed at half-time in Wednesday night's meeting <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/2013/apr/16/arsenal-everton-premier-league-match-report\" title=\"\">between Arsenal and Everton at the Emirates</a>.</p><p>Mirallas appeared to spray water over his opponent as the two teams left the field for the interval, prompting a visibly annoyed Wilshere to confront Mirallas, leading to a brief scuffle in the tunnel. But the referee, Neil Swarbrick, felt the incident needed no further action.</p><p>This will come as a boost for both sides in their respective pushes for Champions League qualification. The availability of Wilshere, who has faced lengthy spells on the sidelines through injury, will be welcomed by Arsenal as they try to secure third place, something the player has deemed unacceptable in the long term.</p><p>Similarly, Mirallas, despite missing a couple of months through injury, has demonstrated his importance to David Moyes's side in an impressive start to his Everton career, culminating in two spectacular individual goals in recent games against Stoke and Tottenham that helped maintain the team's European ambitions.</p><p>Although the goalless draw at the Emirates was almost certainly a better result for Everton, who have not beaten Arsenal since 2007, it is a setback to both sides' hopes of a top-four finish.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/2013/apr/17/fulham-chelsea-premier-league\" title=\"\">After Chelsea's win at Fulham on Wednesday</a>, Arsenal dropped to fourth, two points ahead of Spurs, who have a game in hand. Nevertheless, Arsenal's midfielder Aaron Ramsey maintained \"we still have a lot of confidence\" and that his side \"always knew this was going to be a big week\".</p><p>He added: \"We are still unbeaten in a load of games and hopefully we can finish the week off strongly by getting a win against Fulham. That will put us in a strong position. It was important not to lose to Everton.\"</p><p>A win at Craven Cottage would open up a five-point gap on Spurs before they entertain the champions on Sunday.</p><p>Ramsey's team-mate Per Mertesacker, who returned from suspension for Tuesday's match, feels the fight for fourth will not be settled any time soon. The German told Arsenal Player: \"They [Tottenham and Chelsea] play against each other and Everton have tough games as well. It is absolutely tight and hopefully for us we can win our important games, especially when we look at Saturday away at Fulham. That is the next target.\"</p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/arsenal\">Arsenal</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/everton\">Everton</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/jack-wilshere\">Jack Wilshere</a></li></ul></div><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/terms-of-service\">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/feeds\">More Feeds</a></div><p style=\"clear:both\" /><img width='1' height='1' src='http://guardian.co.uk.feedsportal.com/c/34708/f/639039/s/2ad78d94/mf.gif' border='0'/><div class='mf-viral'><table b