1\"/>" "http://feeds.guardian.co.uk/~r/theguardian/football/rss/~3/v8iR6daCp90/celtic-win-scottish-premier-league-title" (20851 60389) old 13 nil nil ((title nil "Celtic crowned Scottish champions") (link nil "http://feeds.guardian.co.uk/~r/theguardian/football/rss/~3/v8iR6daCp90/celtic-win-scottish-premier-league-title") (description nil "<div class=\"track\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hits.guardian.co.uk/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.4/97046?ns=guardian&pageName=Article%3Aceltic-win-scottish-premier-league-title%3A1897015&ch=Football&c3=GU.co.uk&c4=Scottish+Premier+League%2CCeltic+%28Football+club%29%2CInverness+Caledonian+Thistle+%28Football+club%29%2CFootball%2CSport&c5=Scottish+Football&c6=Guardian+staff+and+agencies&c7=2013%2F04%2F21+02%3A38&c8=1897015&c9=Article&c10=Match+report&c13=&c19=GUK&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=Celtic+win+Scottish+Premier+League+title+after+beating+Inverness+4-1&c66=Sport&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FSport%2FFootball%2FScottish+Premier+League\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /></div><p>Neil Lennon said he was looking for a \"joyous\" occasion at Celtic Park on Sunday and so it proved to be after Celtic's win over Inverness guaranteed their second Scottish Premier League title in succession.</p><p>Lennon made one change to his Celtic side for this fixture, with Anthony Stokes, who scored the winner <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/2013/apr/14/dundee-united-celtic-scottish-cup-match-report\" title=\"\">in last week's 4-3 Scottish Cup semi-final win over Dundee United</a> at Hampden, replacing Emilio Izaguirre who started on the bench. The Inverness manager, Terry Butcher, also made one change with Gary Warren in for Danny Devine, who was named among the substitutes.</p><p>After a goalless first half Gary Hooper broke the deadlock 16 minutes into the second. Kris Commons and Joe Ledley combined before Ledley set up Hooper to score his 27th goal of a prolific season from a tight angle. Five minutes later, the goal provider turned goal scorer after Ledley converted Mikael Lustig's low cross to double Celtic's lead.</p><p>Second-placed Motherwell's 3-1 victory at Dundee United on Friday night meant that Lennon's team needed just one point from the game to take the league title but they all but ensured all three were theirs with their third goal in the space of 15 minutes. Once again, Commons was involved and his cross was wonderfully flicked in at the near post by the former Scunthorpe United striker. The substitute Georgios Samaras added a gloss to the scoreline with a terrific solo effort that was thumped in off the bar with two minutes of normal time remaining.</p><p>A late goal from Aaron Doran spoiled Celtic's clean sheet but not the day for Lennon, his side and supporters.</p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/scottishpremierleague\">Scottish Premier League</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/celtic\">Celtic</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/invernesscaledonianthistle\">Inverness Caledonian Thistle</a></li></ul></div><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/terms-of-service\">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/feeds\">More Feeds</a></div><p style=\"clear:both\" /><img width='1' height='1' src='http://guardian.co.uk.feedsportal.com/c/34708/f/639039/s/2afa9573/mf.gif' border='0'/><div class='mf-viral'><table border='0'><tr><td valign='middle'><a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/twitter/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F21%2Fceltic-win-scottish-premier-league-title&t=Celtic+crowned+Scottish+champions\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/twitter.png\" 