nemouth promoted to the Championship<br />• Gillingham secure League Two title</p><h2><strong>Party time at Portsmouth after loss of 10 points </strong></h2><p>Portsmouth celebrated their first match since coming out of administration by beating play-off chasing Sheffield United 3-0 – a symbolic first step to recovery after 14 turbulent months.</p><p>The 2008 FA Cup winners had their relegation to League Two confirmed on Tuesday, but the supporters' trust takeover, completed on Friday, and the news that their 10-point deduction will be applied to this season's total rather than held over, gave the club a long‑overdue feeling of optimism, which was reflected by a new plaque on display at the ground.</p><p>Shaun Cooper gave the home side the lead against United, David Connolly scored the second and Jed Wallace made it 3-0 with a six-yard finish.</p><p>Portsmouth's caretaker manager, Guy Whittingham, said: \"We put in a lot of hard work and it paid off. I was delighted for the fans who have backed us all season and it was a fantastic atmosphere. The players have worked so hard since we got this group together.\"</p><p>Greg Clarke, chairman of the Football League, said they would monitor the club's rebuilding process next season: \"The supporters' trust have galvanised the club's fans and the city behind their cause. However, the hard work is only just beginning and we will continue working with the new owners to help them establish a sustainable future.\" <strong>PA</strong></p><p></p><h2><strong>Bournemouth up while Scunthorpe hold on </strong></h2><p><strong>Bournemouth</strong> secured promotion to the Championship thanks to a combination of their record eighth successive league victory and <strong>Brentford</strong>'s failure to beat <strong>Hartlepool</strong>. Bournemouth's 3-1 home win over <strong>Carlisle</strong>, with goals from Steve Cook, Harry Arter and Brett Pitman, completed an astonishing turnaround since Eddie Howe returned to the club as manager in October.</p><p><strong>Doncaster</strong>, though, threw away their chance of sealing promotion after they were beaten 1-0 by <strong>Notts County</strong>.</p><p>At the other end, <strong>Scunthorpe</strong> took their battle to avoid following <strong>Portsmouth</strong>, <strong>Hartlepool</strong> and <strong>Bury</strong> into League Two to the final day of the season after securing a vital 1-0 win away at <strong>MK Dons</strong>. Karl Hawley's first-half goal, and a fine performance from Scunthorpe's goalkeeper, Sam Slocombe, secured the victory, and takes them to within three points of fifth-bottom <strong>Colchester</strong>. <strong>PA</strong></p><p></p><h2><strong>Gills take title as fight at&nbsp;the bottom hots up </strong></h2><p><strong>Gillingham</strong> secured the League Two title despite surrendering a two-goal lead at home to <strong>AFC Wimbledon</strong>. The 2-2 draw was enough to give Gillingham their first league title in 49 years.</p><p>Port Vale have all but joined them in securing promotion after Lee Collins's late own goal for <strong>Northampton </strong>gave them a 2-2 draw, leaving them three points clear of Cheltenham in fourth with a goal difference of 28 in their favour ahead of the final day.</p><p>The point at Gillingham left Wimbledon in the relegation zone, making them one of seven clubs who could go down on the final day of the season. Six points separate <strong>Torquay</strong> in 18th and bottom club <strong>Aldershot</strong>, who took their fight for survival to the last day with a vital home win over <strong>Dagenham</strong> – one of the other clubs on the brink of the drop. <strong>PA</strong></p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/leagueonefootball\">League One</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/portsmouth\">Portsmouth</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/leaguetwofootball\">League Two</a></li></ul></div><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/terms-of-service\">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/feeds\">More Feeds</a></div><p style=\"clear:both\" /><img width='1' height='1' src='http://guardian.co.uk.feedsportal.com/c/34708/f/639039/s/2af60648/mf.gif' border='0'/><div class='mf-viral'><table border='0'><tr><td valign='middle'><a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/twitter/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F20%2Ffootball-league-roundup-portsmouth-party&t=Football+League+roundup%3A+Portsmouth+party+after+losing+10+points\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/twitter.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/facebook/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F20%2Ffootball-league-roundup-portsmouth-party&t=Football+League+roundup%3A+Portsmouth+party+after+losing+10+points\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/facebook.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/linkedin/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F20%2Ffootball-league-roundup-portsmouth-party&t=Football+League+roundup%3A+Portsmouth+party+after+losing+10+points\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/linkedin.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/gplus/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F20%2Ffootball-league-roundup-portsmouth-party&t=Football+League+roundup%3A+Portsmouth+party+after+losing+10+points\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/googleplus.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/email/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F20%2Ffootball-league-roundup-portsmouth-party&t=Football+League+roundup%3A+Portsmouth+party+after+losing+10+points\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/email.png\" border=\"0\" /></a></td></tr></table></div><br/><br/><a href=\"http://da.feedsportal.com/r/164016215151/u/49/f/639039/c/34708/s/2af60648/kg/355/a2.htm\"><img src=\"http://da.feedsportal.com/r/164016215151/u/49/f/639039/c/34708/s/2af60648/kg/355/a2.img\" border=\"0\"/></a><img width=\"1\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://pi.feedsportal.com/r/164016215151/u/49/f/639039/c/34708/s/2af60648/kg/355/a2t.img\" border=\"0\"/><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/theguardian/football/rss/~4/tjjeNAfwE54\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football")) "League Two") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football")) "Football") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport")) "Sport") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/tone")) "News") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football")) "League One") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football")) "Portsmouth") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/publication")) "The Observer") (pubDate nil "Sat, 20 Apr 2013 21:52:44 GMT") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/2013/apr/20/football-league-roundup-portsmouth-party") (dc:creator nil) (dc:subject nil "Football") (dc:date nil "2013-04-20T23:14:20Z") (dc:type nil "Article") (dc:identifier nil "407578255") (media:keywords nil "League One, Portsmouth, League Two, Football, Sport") (media:content ((height . "84") (lang . " ") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "140") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Football/Pix/pictures/2013/4/20/1366494702442/A-Portsmouth-fan-with-a-f-003.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Frances Leader/Action Images") (media:description nil "Portsmouth supporters now own 