uTube Yakety Sax remixes.</p><p></p><h2>LINE OF THE DAY</h2><p></p><p><strong>Ian Holloway: </strong>under pressure as Palace's backward momentum continues, but still rolling out the post-match comedy. \"We've got to tweak the nose of fear, put an ice cube down the vest of terror.\"</p><p></p><h2>BOYBAND OF THE DAY</h2><p>For reasons that remain unclear, ex-Fulham legend <strong>Luis Boa Morte</strong> provided the half-time entertainment at Craven Cottage alongside<strong> JLS member Oritsé Williams</strong>.</p><p></p><h2>WORST COMEBACK</h2><p>Fulham's <strong>Steve Sidwell</strong>: a straight red 12 minutes after a three-match ban ended.</p><p></p><h2>GROUND OF THE DAY</h2><p>Wycombe almost spoiled the party during Barnet's last ever match at <strong>Underhill</strong>, only for Joel Grant to have his stoppage-time penalty saved. In the end, Jake Hyde's goal in the 81st minute was enough.</p><p></p><h2>PLUG OF THE DAY</h2><p>It's not hard to work out why <strong>Rio Ferdinand</strong> has been given work as a pundit. \"Dont pi$$ me off, Tell me there is some live football on tv 2day????\" he tweeted. Were Burnley v Cardiff and Hartlepool v Brentford not good enough for Rio?</p><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/terms-of-service\">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/feeds\">More Feeds</a></div><p style=\"clear:both\" /><img width='1' height='1' src='http://guardian.co.uk.feedsportal.com/c/34708/f/639039/s/2af6728e/mf.gif' border='0'/><div class='mf-viral'><table border='0'><tr><td valign='middle'><a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/twitter/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F20%2Fsaturday-sundae-norwich-bennett-reading&t=Saturday+Sundae%3A+Norwich+serve+up+a+double+Bennett+for+Read